        "gml_Script_window_set_cursor_init",
        "gml_Script_window_set_cursor_normal",
        "gml_Script_window_set_cursor_surface_part",
        "gml_Script____struct___902",
        "gml_Script_anon@1277@gml_Script_window_set_cursor_surface_part",
        "gml_Script_anon@1366@gml_Script_window_set_cursor_surface_part",
        "gml_Script_window_set_cursor_surface",
        "gml_Script_window_set_cursor_sprite",
        "gml_Script_window_set_cursor_sprite_ext",
        "gml_Script_window_set_cursor_init_dll",
        "gml_Script_window_set_cursor_impl_1",
        "gml_Script_window_set_cursor_impl",
        "shd_anchor_shadow",
        "#define LOWPREC lowp\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW] * pos;\n\t\tfloat fogfactor = ((viewpos.z - gm_FogStart) * gm_RcpFogRange);\n\t\treturn fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough vertex shader\r\n//\r\nattribute vec3 in_Position;                  // (x,y,z)\r\n//attribute vec3 in_Normal;                  // (x,y,z)     unused in this shader.\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;                    // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord;              // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n    vec4 object_space_pos = vec4( in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n    gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * object_space_pos;\r\n    \r\n    v_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n}\r\n",
        "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough fragment shader\r\n//\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nuniform float pixel_height;\r\nuniform float pixel_width;\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n    vec2 offsetx;\r\n    offsetx = vec2(pixel_width * 2.0, 0);\r\n    vec2 offsety;\r\n    offsety = vec2(0, pixel_height * 2.0);\r\n  \r\n\tvec4 color = texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord);\r\n\tfloat o_alpha = color.a;\r\n    float alpha = color.a;\r\n    alpha = max(alpha, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord - offsetx).a);\r\n    alpha = max(alpha, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord - offsety).a);\r\n    alpha = max(alpha, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord - offsety - offsetx).a);\r\n\tgl_FragColor = v_vColour * color;\r\n\tif (alpha - o_alpha == 0.0) {\r\n\t\tgl_FragColor = v_vColour * color;\r\n\t} else {\r\n\t\tgl_FragColor = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.25);\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW] * pos;\n\t\tfloat fogfactor = ((viewpos.z - gm_FogStart) * gm_RcpFogRange);\n\t\treturn fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough vertex shader\r\n//\r\nattribute vec3 in_Position;                  // (x,y,z)\r\n//attribute vec3 in_Normal;                  // (x,y,z)     unused in this shader.\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;                    // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord;              // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n    vec4 object_space_pos = vec4( in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n    gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * object_space_pos;\r\n    \r\n    v_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough fragment shader\r\n//\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nuniform float pixel_height;\r\nuniform float pixel_width;\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n    vec2 offsetx;\r\n    offsetx = vec2(pixel_width * 2.0, 0);\r\n    vec2 offsety;\r\n    offsety = vec2(0, pixel_height * 2.0);\r\n  \r\n\tvec4 color = texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord);\r\n\tfloat o_alpha = color.a;\r\n    float alpha = color.a;\r\n    alpha = max(alpha, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord - offsetx).a);\r\n    alpha = max(alpha, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord - offsety).a);\r\n    alpha = max(alpha, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord - offsety - offsetx).a);\r\n\tgl_FragColor = v_vColour * color;\r\n\tif (alpha - o_alpha == 0.0) {\r\n\t\tgl_FragColor = v_vColour * color;\r\n\t} else {\r\n\t\tgl_FragColor = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.25);\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n",

posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough vertex shader\r\n//\r\nattribute vec3 in_Position; // (x,y,z)\r\n// attribute vec3 in_Normal;                  // (x,y,z)     unused in this shader.\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;       // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord; // (u,v)\r\n\r\nuniform float u_display_ratio;\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vPosition;\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n    vec3 position = vec3(\r\n        floor(in_Position.x * u_display_ratio) / u_display_ratio,\r\n        floor(in_Position.y * u_display_ratio) / u_display_ratio,\r\n        in_Position.z\r\n    );\r\n\r\n    gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * vec4(position, 1.0);\r\n\r\n    v_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n    v_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vPosition = in_Position.xy;\r\n}\r\n",
        "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vPosition;\r\n\r\n// incoming palette\r\nuniform sampler2D u_pal_tex;\r\n\r\n// our uvs for the palette shader on the texsheet\r\n// this is really a (vec2, vec2) of left_top, right_bottom\r\nuniform vec4 u_uvs;\r\nuniform float u_index;\r\nuniform vec2 u_pixel_size;\r\n\r\n// the clip space\r\nuniform vec4 u_clip_space;\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n  // run the clip...\r\n  if (v_vPosition.x < u_clip_space.x || v_vPosition.y < u_clip_space.y ||\r\n      v_vPosition.x > u_clip_space.z || v_vPosition.y > u_clip_space.w) {\r\n    discard;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  vec4 output_color = texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord);\r\n\r\n  // multiply my color by stuff?\r\n  float alpha = output_color.a * v_vColour.a;\r\n\r\n  if (alpha < 0.05) {\r\n    discard;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  // Iterate over our texture going down.....\r\n  for (float lookup_y = u_uvs.y; lookup_y < u_uvs.w;\r\n       lookup_y += u_pixel_size.y) {\r\n    // start walking down....\r\n    vec2 test_pos = vec2(u_uvs.x, lookup_y);\r\n    vec4 lookup_color = texture2D(u_pal_tex, test_pos);\r\n    bool did_find_color = distance(lookup_color.rgb, output_color.rgb) < 0.001;\r\n\r\n    if (did_find_color) {\r\n      // and reassigning the color...\r\n      vec4 requested_color = texture2D(\r\n          u_pal_tex, vec2(u_uvs.x + u_pixel_size.x * u_index, lookup_y));\r\n      output_color = vec4(requested_color.rgb, alpha);\r\n\r\n      // and we OUTTIE\r\n      break;\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  // draw me baybe\r\n  gl_FragColor = vec4(output_color.rgb * v_vColour.rgb * alpha, alpha);\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough vertex shader\r\n//\r\nattribute vec3 in_Position; // (x,y,z)\r\n// attribute vec3 in_Normal;                  // (x,y,z)     unused in this shader.\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;       // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord; // (u,v)\r\n\r\nuniform float u_display_ratio;\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vPosition;\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n    vec3 position = vec3(\r\n        floor(in_Position.x * u_display_ratio) / u_display_ratio,\r\n        floor(in_Position.y * u_display_ratio) / u_display_ratio,\r\n        in_Position.z\r\n    );\r\n\r\n    gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * vec4(position, 1.0);\r\n\r\n    v_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n    v_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vPosition = in_Position.xy;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vPosition;\r\n\r\n// incoming palette\r\nuniform sampler2D u_pal_tex;\r\n\r\n// our uvs for the palette shader on the texsheet\r\n// this is really a (vec2, vec2) of left_top, right_bottom\r\nuniform vec4 u_uvs;\r\nuniform float u_index;\r\nuniform vec2 u_pixel_size;\r\n\r\n// the clip space\r\nuniform vec4 u_clip_space;\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n  // run the clip...\r\n  if (v_vPosition.x < u_clip_space.x || v_vPosition.y < u_clip_space.y ||\r\n      v_vPosition.x > u_clip_space.z || v_vPosition.y > u_clip_space.w) {\r\n    discard;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  vec4 output_color = texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord);\r\n\r\n  // multiply my color by stuff?\r\n  float alpha = output_color.a * v_vColour.a;\r\n\r\n  if (alpha < 0.05) {\r\n    discard;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  // Iterate over our texture going down.....\r\n  for (float lookup_y = u_uvs.y; lookup_y < u_uvs.w;\r\n       lookup_y += u_pixel_size.y) {\r\n    // start walking down....\r\n    vec2 test_pos = vec2(u_uvs.x, lookup_y);\r\n    vec4 lookup_color = texture2D(u_pal_tex, test_pos);\r\n    bool did_find_color = distance(lookup_color.rgb, output_color.rgb) < 0.001;\r\n\r\n    if (did_find_color) {\r\n      // and reassigning the color...\r\n      vec4 requested_color = texture2D(\r\n          u_pal_tex, vec2(u_uvs.x + u_pixel_size.x * u_index, lookup_y));\r\n      output_color = vec4(requested_color.rgb, alpha);\r\n\r\n      // and we OUTTIE\r\n      break;\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  // draw me baybe\r\n  gl_FragColor = vec4(output_color.rgb * v_vColour.rgb * alpha, alpha);\r\n}\r\n",

        "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\n// incoming palette\r\nuniform sampler2D u_lut_tex;\r\n\r\n// the texel size of the thing\r\nuniform vec2 u_pixel_size;\r\n\r\n// our uvs for the palette shader on the texsheet\r\n// this is really a (vec2, vec2) of left_top, right_bottom\r\nuniform vec4 u_uvs;\r\n\r\n// the x_multiple to get to the color. This is in ints really.\r\nuniform float u_index;\r\n\r\nfloat bm_overlay(float base, float blend) {\r\n  if (base <= 0.5) {\r\n    return 2.0 * base * blend;\r\n  } else {\r\n    return 1.0 - 2.0 * (1.0 - base) * (1.0 - blend);\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nvec3 bm_overlay(vec3 base, vec3 blend) {\r\n  return vec3(bm_overlay(base.r, blend.r), bm_overlay(base.g, blend.g),\r\n              bm_overlay(base.b, blend.b));\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n  vec4 base_color = texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord);\r\n\r\n  float vert_offset = floor(base_color.r * 255.0);\r\n  float height = u_uvs.w - u_uvs.y;\r\n\r\n  float x_pos = u_uvs.x + u_index * u_pixel_size.x + (u_pixel_size.x / 2.0);\r\n  float y_pos = u_uvs.y + vert_offset * u_pixel_size.y + (u_pixel_size.y / 2.0);\r\n\r\n  vec4 base = vec4(texture2D(u_lut_tex, vec2(x_pos, y_pos)).rgb, base_color.a);\r\n  vec3 raw_overlay = bm_overlay(base.rgb, v_vColour.rgb);\r\n  vec3 double_blended =\r\n      ((raw_overlay.rgb * v_vColour.a + base.rgb * base.a) + base.rgb) / 2.0;\r\n\r\n  gl_FragColor = vec4(double_blended, base.a);\r\n}\r\n",

        "shd_day_night",
        "#define LOWPREC lowp\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW  gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn         "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\n\r\nuniform vec4 u_VividColor;\r\nuniform vec3 u_Levels;\r\n\r\nfloat blendColorBurn(float base, float blend) {\r\n    return (blend == 0.0) ? blend : max((1.0 - ((1.0 - base) / blend)), 0.0);\r\n}\r\n\r\nfloat blendColorDodge(float base, float blend) {\r\n    return (blend == 1.0) ? blend : min(base / (1.0 - blend), 1.0);\r\n}\r\n\r\nfloat blendVividLight(float base, float blend) {\r\n    return (blend < 0.5) ? blendColorBurn(base, (2.0 * blend)) : blendColorDodge(base, (2.0 * (blend - 0.5)));\r\n}\r\n\r\nvec3 blendVividLight(vec3 base, vec3 blend) {\r\n    return vec3(blendVividLight(base.r, blend.r), blendVividLight(base.g, blend.g),\r\n                blendVividLight(base.b, blend.b));\r\n}\r\n\r\n// vec3 blend_multiply(vec3 base, vec3 blend, float strength) {\r\n//     return base * blend * strength + base * (1.0 - strength);\r\n//     //     DEST_COLOR * (SRC) * strength + base * (1.0 - strength);\r\n// }\r\n\r\nvec3 gammaCorrect(vec3 color, float gamma) {\r\n    return pow(color, vec3(1.0 / gamma));\r\n}\r\n\r\nvec3 levelRange(vec3 color, float minInput, float maxInput) {\r\n    return min(max(color - vec3(minInput), vec3(0.0)) / (vec3(maxInput) - vec3(minInput)), vec3(1.0));\r\n}\r\n\r\nvec3 finalLevels(vec3 color, float minInput, float gamma, float maxInput) {\r\n    return gammaCorrect(levelRange(color, minInput, maxInput), gamma);\r\n}\r\n\r\nfloat max3(vec3 v) {\r\n    return max(max(v.x, v.y), v.z);\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n    vec4 base = v_vColour * texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord);\r\n    vec3 base_v3 = vec3(base);\r\n\r\n    // VIVID\r\n    vec3 vivid =\r\n        blendVividLight(base_v3, u_VividColor.rgb) * u_VividColor.a +\r\n        base_v3 * min(1.0 - u_VividColor.a, 1.0);\r\n\r\n    // levels adjustment\r\n    vec3 levels_adjustment = finalLevels(vivid, u_Levels.x, u_Levels.y, u_Levels.z);\r\n\r\n    gl_FragColor = vec4(levels_adjustment, 1.0);\r\n}\r\n",

fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough vertex shader\r\n//\r\nattribute vec3 in_Position; // (x,y,z)\r\n// attribute vec3 in_Normal;                  // (x,y,z)     unused in this shader.\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;       // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord; // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n    vec4 object_space_pos = vec4(in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n    gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * object_space_pos;\r\n\r\n    v_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\n\r\nuniform vec4 u_VividColor;\r\nuniform vec3 u_Levels;\r\n\r\nfloat blendColorBurn(float base, float blend) {\r\n    return (blend == 0.0) ? blend : max((1.0 - ((1.0 - base) / blend)), 0.0);\r\n}\r\n\r\nfloat blendColorDodge(float base, float blend) {\r\n    return (blend == 1.0) ? blend : min(base / (1.0 - blend), 1.0);\r\n}\r\n\r\nfloat blendVividLight(float base, float blend) {\r\n    return (blend < 0.5) ? blendColorBurn(base, (2.0 * blend)) : blendColorDodge(base, (2.0 * (blend - 0.5)));\r\n}\r\n\r\nvec3 blendVividLight(vec3 base, vec3 blend) {\r\n    return vec3(blendVividLight(base.r, blend.r), blendVividLight(base.g, blend.g),\r\n                blendVividLight(base.b, blend.b));\r\n}\r\n\r\n// vec3 blend_multiply(vec3 base, vec3 blend, float strength) {\r\n//     return base * blend * strength + base * (1.0 - strength);\r\n//     //     DEST_COLOR * (SRC) * strength + base * (1.0 - strength);\r\n// }\r\n\r\nvec3 gammaCorrect(vec3 color, float gamma) {\r\n    return pow(color, vec3(1.0 / gamma));\r\n}\r\n\r\nvec3 levelRange(vec3 color, float minInput, float maxInput) {\r\n    return min(max(color - vec3(minInput), vec3(0.0)) / (vec3(maxInput) - vec3(minInput)), vec3(1.0));\r\n}\r\n\r\nvec3 finalLevels(vec3 color, float minInput, float gamma, float maxInput) {\r\n    return gammaCorrect(levelRange(color, minInput, maxInput), gamma);\r\n}\r\n\r\nfloat max3(vec3 v) {\r\n    return max(max(v.x, v.y), v.z);\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n    vec4 base = v_vColour * texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord);\r\n    vec3 base_v3 = vec3(base);\r\n\r\n    // VIVID\r\n    vec3 vivid =\r\n        blendVividLight(base_v3, u_VividColor.rgb) * u_VividColor.a +\r\n        base_v3 * min(1.0 - u_VividColor.a, 1.0);\r\n\r\n    // levels adjustment\r\n    vec3 levels_adjustment = finalLevels(vivid, u_Levels.x, u_Levels.y, u_Levels.z);\r\n\r\n    gl_FragColor = vec4(levels_adjustment, 1.0);\r\n}\r\n",

MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough vertex shader\r\n//\r\nattribute vec3 in_Position; // (x,y,z)\r\n// attribute vec3 in_Normal;                  // (x,y,z)     unused in this\r\n// shader.\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;       // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord; // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n  vec4 object_space_pos =\r\n      vec4(in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n  gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * object_space_pos;\r\n\r\n  v_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n  v_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nfloat divide(float base, float blend) {\r\n  return blend > 0.0 ? min(1.0, base / blend) : 1.0;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvec3 divide(vec3 base, vec3 blend) {\r\n  return vec3(divide(base.r, blend.r), divide(base.g, blend.g),\r\n              divide(base.b, blend.b));\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n  vec4 base_color = texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord);\r\n\r\n  gl_FragColor = vec4(base_color.rgb / v_vColour.rgb, v_vColour.a * base_color.a);\r\n}\r\n",
        "shd_layer_alpha",
        "#define LOWPREC lowp\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z         "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nuniform float pixelH;\r\nuniform float pixelW;\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n  vec2 offsetx = vec2(pixelW, 0);\r\n  vec2 offsety = vec2(0, pixelH);\r\n\r\n  vec4 img = texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord);\r\n  vec4 color = img;\r\n\r\n  color.a = max(color.a, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord + offsetx).a);\r\n  color.a = max(color.a, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord - offsetx).a);\r\n  color.a = max(color.a, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord + offsety).a);\r\n  color.a = max(color.a, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord - offsety).a);\r\n\r\n  if (color.a != img.a) {\r\n    color.rgb = v_vColour.rgb;\r\n  }\r\n  gl_FragColor = color;\r\n}\r\n",

        "shd_petals_spring",
        "#define LOWPREC lowp\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW] * pos;\n\t\tfloat fogfactor = ((viewpos.z - gm_FogStart) * gm_RcpFogRange);\n\t\treturn fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nattribute vec3 in_Position;                  // (x,y,z)\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;                    // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord;              // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nuniform float u_time;\r\nuniform vec4 u_camera_bbox;\r\n\r\nconst vec2 PADDING = vec2(13.0, 13.0);\r\n\r\nconst float ANIMATION_SPEED = 6.0;\r\n\r\nfloat wrap(float current, float min, float max) {\r\n\treturn (current - min) - floor((current - min) / (max - min)) * (max - min) + min;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Where am I?\r\n\tvec4 world_pos = vec4(in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n\tvec2 cell_pos = vec2(floor(world_pos.x / PADDING.x), floor(world_pos.y / PADDING.y));\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Add an offset, as a treat\r\n\tvec2 offset = vec2( // Yes, the flip is on purpose, it makes it more unique\r\n\t\tmod(cell_pos.y, PADDING.y) - (PADDING.x / 2.0),\r\n\t\tmod(cell_pos.x, PADDING.x) - (PADDING.y / 2.0)\r\n\t); \r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Move that sucka\r\n\tfloat speed = (mod(cell_pos.x, 3.0) + 1.0) * 0.1;\r\n\tfloat angle = (in_Colour.r * 256.0) / 40.0; // the red channel holds the radian\r\n\tvec2 delta = vec2(cos(angle) * speed, -sin(angle) * speed);\r\n\tworld_pos.x = wrap(\r\n\t\tworld_pos.x + offset.x + delta.x * u_time,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.r - PADDING.x,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.b + PADDING.x\r\n\t);\r\n\tworld_pos.y = wrap(\r\n\t\tworld_pos.y + offset.y + delta.y * u_time,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.g - PADDING.y,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.a + PADDING.y\r\n\t);\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Set some jazz\r\n\tv_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n\r\n\t// wrap animation\r\n\tfloat tex_x_coord = mod(floor((u_time / ANIMATION_SPEED) + in_Colour.g), 11.0) / 11.0;\r\n\tv_vTexcoord = vec2(in_TextureCoord.x + tex_x_coord, in_TextureCoord.y);\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Check to hide\r\n\tfloat multip = 1.0 - float(\r\n\t\t   world_pos.x < u_camera_bbox.x \r\n\t\t|| world_pos.y < u_camera_bbox.y\r\n\t\t|| world_pos.x > u_camera_bbox.z \r\n\t\t|| world_pos.y > u_camera_bbox.w \r\n\t);\r\n\tv_vColour.a = multip;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Output\r\n\tgl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * world_pos;\r\n}\r\n",
        "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough fragment shader\r\n//\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n\tgl_FragColor = texture2D( gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord );\r\n\tgl_FragColor.a *= v_vColour.a;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW] * pos;\n\t\tfloat fogfactor = ((viewpos.z - gm_FogStart) * gm_RcpFogRange);\n\t\treturn fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\nattribute vec3 in_Position;                  // (x,y,z)\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;                    // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord;              // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nuniform float u_time;\r\nuniform vec4 u_camera_bbox;\r\n\r\nconst vec2 PADDING = vec2(13.0, 13.0);\r\n\r\nconst float ANIMATION_SPEED = 6.0;\r\n\r\nfloat wrap(float current, float min, float max) {\r\n\treturn (current - min) - floor((current - min) / (max - min)) * (max - min) + min;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Where am I?\r\n\tvec4 world_pos = vec4(in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n\tvec2 cell_pos = vec2(floor(world_pos.x / PADDING.x), floor(world_pos.y / PADDING.y));\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Add an offset, as a treat\r\n\tvec2 offset = vec2( // Yes, the flip is on purpose, it makes it more unique\r\n\t\tmod(cell_pos.y, PADDING.y) - (PADDING.x / 2.0),\r\n\t\tmod(cell_pos.x, PADDING.x) - (PADDING.y / 2.0)\r\n\t); \r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Move that sucka\r\n\tfloat speed = (mod(cell_pos.x, 3.0) + 1.0) * 0.1;\r\n\tfloat angle = (in_Colour.r * 256.0) / 40.0; // the red channel holds the radian\r\n\tvec2 delta = vec2(cos(angle) * speed, -sin(angle) * speed);\r\n\tworld_pos.x = wrap(\r\n\t\tworld_pos.x + offset.x + delta.x * u_time,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.r - PADDING.x,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.b + PADDING.x\r\n\t);\r\n\tworld_pos.y = wrap(\r\n\t\tworld_pos.y + offset.y + delta.y * u_time,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.g - PADDING.y,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.a + PADDING.y\r\n\t);\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Set some jazz\r\n\tv_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n\r\n\t// wrap animation\r\n\tfloat tex_x_coord = mod(floor((u_time / ANIMATION_SPEED) + in_Colour.g), 11.0) / 11.0;\r\n\tv_vTexcoord = vec2(in_TextureCoord.x + tex_x_coord, in_TextureCoord.y);\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Check to hide\r\n\tfloat multip = 1.0 - float(\r\n\t\t   world_pos.x < u_camera_bbox.x \r\n\t\t|| world_pos.y < u_camera_bbox.y\r\n\t\t|| world_pos.x > u_camera_bbox.z \r\n\t\t|| world_pos.y > u_camera_bbox.w \r\n\t);\r\n\tv_vColour.a = multip;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Output\r\n\tgl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * world_pos;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough fragment shader\r\n//\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n\tgl_FragColor = texture2D( gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord );\r\n\tgl_FragColor.a *= v_vColour.a;\r\n}\r\n",
        "shd_petals",
        "#define LOWPREC lowp\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW] * pos;\n\t\tfloat fogfactor = ((viewpos.z - gm_FogStart) * gm_RcpFogRange);\n\t\treturn fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nattribute vec3 in_Position;                  // (x,y,z)\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;                    // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord;              // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nuniform float u_time;\r\nuniform vec4 u_camera_bbox;\r\nuniform float u_ratio;\r\n\r\nconst vec2 PADDING = vec2(9.0, 9.0);\r\n\r\nfloat wrap(float current, float min, float max) {\r\n\treturn (current - min) - floor((current - min) / (max - min)) * (max - min) + min;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n\t// Where am I?\r\n\tvec4 world_pos = vec4(in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n\tvec2 cell_pos = vec2(floor(world_pos.x / PADDING.x), floor(world_pos.y / PADDING.y));\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Add an offset, as a treat\r\n\tvec2 offset = vec2( // Yes, the flip is on purpose, it makes it more unique\r\n\t\tmod(cell_pos.y, PADDING.y) - (PADDING.x / 2.0),\r\n\t\tmod(cell_pos.x, PADDING.x) - (PADDING.y / 2.0)\r\n\t); \r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Move that sucka\r\n\tfloat speed = (mod(cell_pos.x, 3.0) + 1.0) * 0.1;\r\n\tfloat angle = (in_Colour.r * 256.0) / 40.0; // the red channel holds the radian\r\n\tvec2 delta = vec2(cos(angle) * speed, -sin(angle) * speed);\r\n\tworld_pos.x = wrap(\r\n\t\tworld_pos.x + offset.x + delta.x * u_time,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.r - PADDING.x,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.b + PADDING.x\r\n\t);\r\n\tworld_pos.y = wrap(\r\n\t\tworld_pos.y + offset.y + delta.y * u_time,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.g - PADDING.y,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.a + PADDING.y\r\n\t);\r\n\r\n\t// how about a little floor love\r\n\tworld_pos.x = floor(world_pos.x * u_ratio) / u_ratio;\r\n\tworld_pos.y = floor(world_pos.y * u_ratio) / u_ratio;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Set some jazz\r\n\tv_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n\tv_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Check to hide\r\n\tfloat multip = 1.0 - float(\r\n\t\t   world_pos.x < u_camera_bbox.x \r\n\t\t|| world_pos.y < u_camera_bbox.y\r\n\t\t|| world_pos.x > u_camera_bbox.z \r\n\t\t|| world_pos.y > u_camera_bbox.w \r\n\t);\r\n\tv_vColour.a = multip;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Output\r\n\tgl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * world_pos;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW] * pos;\n\t\tfloat fogfactor = ((viewpos.z - gm_FogStart) * gm_RcpFogRange);\n\t\treturn fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\nattribute vec3 in_Position;                  // (x,y,z)\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;                    // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord;              // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nuniform float u_time;\r\nuniform vec4 u_camera_bbox;\r\nuniform float u_ratio;\r\n\r\nconst vec2 PADDING = vec2(9.0, 9.0);\r\n\r\nfloat wrap(float current, float min, float max) {\r\n\treturn (current - min) - floor((current - min) / (max - min)) * (max - min) + min;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n\t// Where am I?\r\n\tvec4 world_pos = vec4(in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n\tvec2 cell_pos = vec2(floor(world_pos.x / PADDING.x), floor(world_pos.y / PADDING.y));\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Add an offset, as a treat\r\n\tvec2 offset = vec2( // Yes, the flip is on purpose, it makes it more unique\r\n\t\tmod(cell_pos.y, PADDING.y) - PADDING.x,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.b + PADDING.x\r\n\t);\r\n\tworld_pos.y = wrap(\r\n\t\tworld_pos.y + offset.y + delta.y * u_time,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.g - PADDING.y,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.a + PADDING.y\r\n\t);\r\n\r\n\t// how about a little floor love\r\n\tworld_pos.x = floor(world_pos.x * u_ratio) / u_ratio;\r\n\tworld_pos.y = floor(world_pos.y * u_ratio) / u_ratio;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Set some jazz\r\n\tv_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n\tv_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Check to hide\r\n\tfloat multip = 1.0 - float(\r\n\t\t   world_pos.x < u_camera_bbox.x \r\n\t\t|| world_pos.y < u_camera_bbox.y\r\n\t\t|| world_pos.x > u_camera_bbox.z \r\n\t\t|| world_pos.y > u_camera_bbox.w \r\n\t);\r\n\tv_vColour.a = multip;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Output\r\n\tgl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * world_pos;\r\n}\r\n",

        "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\n// incoming palette\r\nuniform sampler2D u_lut_tex;\r\n\r\n// the texel size of the thing\r\nuniform vec2 u_pixel_size;\r\n\r\n// our uvs for the palette shader on the texsheet\r\n// this is really a (vec2, vec2) of left_top, right_bottom\r\nuniform vec4 u_uvs;\r\n\r\n// the x_multiple to get to the color.         "#define LOWPREC lowp\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW] * pos;\n\t\tfloat fogfactor = ((viewpos.z - gm_FogStart) * gm_RcpFogRange);\n\t\treturn fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nattribute vec3 in_Position;                  // (x,y,z)\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;                    // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord;              // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nuniform float u_time;\r\nuniform vec4 u_camera_bbox;\r\nuniform vec4 u_world_bbox;\r\nuniform vec2 u_padding;\r\n\r\nfloat wrap(float current, float min, float max) {\r\n\treturn (current - min) - floor((current - min) / (max - min)) * (max - min) + min;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t// Where am I?\r\n\t\tvec4 world_pos = vec4(in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n\t\tworld_pos.xy -= u_camera_bbox.xy;\r\n\t\t/*vec2 cell_pos = vec2(floor(world_pos.x / u_padding.x), floor(world_pos.y / u_padding.y));\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t// Add an offset, as a treat\r\n\t\tvec2 offset = vec2(mod((cell_pos.y * 100.0), u_padding.y) - (u_padding.x / 2.0), mod((cell_pos.x * 100.0), u_padding.x) - (u_padding.y / 2.0)); // Yes, the flip is on purpose\r\n\t\t*/\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t// Move that sucka\r\n\t\tfloat speed = 0.2;\r\n\t\tvec2 delta = vec2(cos(0.0) * speed, -sin(0.0) * speed);\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\tworld_pos.x = wrap(\r\n\t\t\tworld_pos.x + delta.x * u_time,\r\n\t\t\tu_world_bbox.r - u_camera_bbox.r - (u_padding.x * 2.0),\r\n\t\t\tu_world_bbox.b - u_camera_bbox.r + (u_padding.x * 2.0)\r\n\t\t);\r\n\t\tworld_pos.y = wrap(world_pos.y + delta.y * u_time,\r\n\t\t\tu_world_bbox.g - u_camera_bbox.g - (u_padding.y * 2.0),\r\n\t\t\tu_world_bbox.a - u_camera_bbox.g + (u_padding.y * 2.0)\r\n\t\t);\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t// Set some jazz\r\n\t\tv_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t// Check to hide\r\n\t\tfloat multip = 1.0 * (1.0 -
