        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW] * pos;\n\t\tfloat fogfactor = ((viewpos.z - gm_FogStart) * gm_RcpFogRange);\n\t\treturn fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\nattribute vec3 in_Position;                  // (x,y,z)\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;                    // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord;              // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nuniform float u_time;\r\nuniform vec4 u_camera_bbox;\r\nuniform vec4 u_world_bbox;\r\nuniform vec2 u_padding;\r\n\r\nfloat wrap(float current, float min, float max) {\r\n\treturn (current - min) - floor((current - min) / (max - min)) * (max - min) + min;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t// Where am I?\r\n\t\tvec4 world_pos = vec4(in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n\t\tworld_pos.xy -= u_camera_bbox.xy;\r\n\t\t/*vec2 cell_pos = vec2(floor(world_pos.x / u_padding.x), floor(world_pos.y / u_padding.y));\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t// Add an offset, as a treat\r\n\t\tvec2 offset = vec2(mod((cell_pos.y * 100.0), u_padding.y) - (u_padding.x / 2.0), mod((cell_pos.x * 100.0), u_padding.x) - (u_padding.y / 2.0)); // Yes, the flip is on purpose\r\n\t\t*/\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t// Move that sucka\r\n\t\tfloat speed = 0.2;\r\n\t\tvec2 delta = vec2(cos(0.0) * speed, -sin(0.0) * speed);\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\tworld_pos.x = wrap(\r\n\t\t\tworld_pos.x + delta.x * u_time,\r\n\t\t\tu_world_bbox.r - u_camera_bbox.r - (u_padding.x * 2.0),\r\n\t\t\tu_world_bbox.b - u_camera_bbox.r + (u_padding.x * 2.0)\r\n\t\t);\r\n\t\tworld_pos.y = wrap(world_pos.y + delta.y * u_time,\r\n\t\t\tu_world_bbox.g - u_camera_bbox.g - (u_padding.y * 2.0),\r\n\t\t\tu_world_bbox.a - u_camera_bbox.g + (u_padding.y * 2.0)\r\n\t\t);\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t// Set some jazz\r\n\t\tv_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t// Check to hide\r\n\t\tfloat multip = 1.0 * (1.0 - float(\r\n\t\t\t\t world_pos.x < u_world_bbox.x - u_camera_bbox.x - u_padding.x \r\n\t\t\t|| world_pos.y < u_world_bbox.y - u_camera_bbox.y - u_padding.y\r\n\t\t\t|| world_pos.x > u_world_bbox.z - u_camera_bbox.x + u_padding.x \r\n\t\t\t|| world_pos.y > u_world_bbox.w - u_camera_bbox.y + u_padding.y \r\n\t\t));\r\n\t\tv_vColour.a = multip;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t// Output\r\n    gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * world_pos;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n    vec4 color = v_vColour * texture2D( gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord );\r\n\r\n    if (color.a < 0.5) {\r\n        discard;\r\n    }\r\n    gl_FragColor = color;\r\n}\r\n",

        "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough fragment shader\r\n//\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nuniform vec4 u_overlay_color;\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n    gl_FragColor = v_vColour * texture2D( gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord );\r\n\t\tgl_FragColor *= u_overlay_color;\r\n}\r\n",

min) - floor((current - min) / (max - min)) * (max - min) + min;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Where am I?\r\n\tvec4 world_pos = vec4(in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n\tvec2 cell_pos = vec2(floor(world_pos.x / padding.x), floor(world_pos.y / padding.y));\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Add an offset, as a treat\r\n\tvec2 offset = vec2( // Yes, the flip is on purpose, it makes it more unique\r\n\t\tmod(cell_pos.y, padding.y) - (padding.x / 2.0),\r\n\t\tmod(cell_pos.x, padding.x) - (padding.y / 2.0)\r\n\t); \r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Prophesize our death\r\n\tfloat death_y = u_camera_bbox.g + (cell_pos.y * padding.y) + 125.0;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Move that sucka\r\n\tfloat speed = mod(cell_pos.x, 3.0) + 3.0;\r\n\tfloat angle = (in_Colour.r * 256.0) / 40.0; // the red channel holds the radian\r\n\tvec2 delta = vec2(cos(angle) * speed, -sin(angle) * speed);\r\n\tworld_pos.x = wrap(\r\n\t\tworld_pos.x + offset.x + delta.x * u_time,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.r - padding.x,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.b + padding.x\r\n\t);\r\n\tworld_pos.y = wrap(\r\n\t\tworld_pos.y + offset.y + delta.y * u_time,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.g - padding.y,\r\n\t\tdeath_y + padding.y\r\n\t);\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Set some jazz\r\n\tv_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n\tv_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Check to hide\r\n\tfloat multip = 0.625 * (1.0 - float(\r\n\t\t\t\tworld_pos.x < u_camera_bbox.x \r\n\t\t|| world_pos.y < u_camera_bbox.y\r\n\t\t|| world_pos.x > u_camera_bbox.z \r\n\t\t|| world_pos.y > death_y\r\n\t));\r\n\tv_vColour.a = multip;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Output\r\n\tgl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * world_pos;\r\n}\r\n",

        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW] * pos;\n\t\tfloat fogfactor = ((viewpos.z - gm_FogStart) * gm_RcpFogRange);\n\t\treturn fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\nattribute vec3 in_Position;                  // (x,y,z)\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;                    // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord;              // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nuniform float u_time;\r\nuniform vec4 u_camera_bbox;\r\n\r\nconst vec2 padding = vec2(10.0, 17.0);\r\n\r\nfloat wrap(float current, float min, float max) {\r\n\treturn (current - min) - floor((current - min) / (max - min)) * (max - min) + min;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Where am I?\r\n\tvec4 world_pos = vec4(in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n\tvec2 cell_pos = vec2(floor(world_pos.x / padding.x), floor(world_pos.y / padding.y));\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Add an offset, as a treat\r\n\tvec2 offset = vec2( // Yes, the flip is on purpose, it makes it more unique\r\n\t\tmod(cell_pos.y, padding.y) - (padding.x / 2.0),\r\n\t\tmod(cell_pos.x, padding.x) - (padding.y / 2.0)\r\n\t); \r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Prophesize our death\r\n\tfloat death_y = u_camera_bbox.g + (cell_pos.y * padding.y) + 125.0;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Move that sucka\r\n\tfloat speed = mod(cell_pos.x, 3.0) + 3.0;\r\n\tfloat angle = (in_Colour.r * 256.0) / 40.0; // the red channel holds the radian\r\n\tvec2 delta = vec2(cos(angle) * speed, -sin(angle) * speed);\r\n\tworld_pos.x = wrap(\r\n\t\tworld_pos.x + offset.x + delta.x * u_time,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.r - padding.x,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.b + padding.x\r\n\t);\r\n\tworld_pos.y = wrap(\r\n\t\tworld_pos.y + offset.y + delta.y * u_time,\r\n\t\tu_camera_bbox.g - padding.y,\r\n\t\tdeath_y + padding.y\r\n\t);\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Set some jazz\r\n\tv_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n\tv_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Check to hide\r\n\tfloat multip = 0.625 * (1.0 - float(\r\n\t\t\t\tworld_pos.x < u_camera_bbox.x \r\n\t\t|| world_pos.y < u_camera_bbox.y\r\n\t\t|| world_pos.x > u_camera_bbox.z \r\n\t\t|| world_pos.y > death_y\r\n\t));\r\n\tv_vColour.a = multip;\r\n\t\t\r\n\t// Output\r\n\tgl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * world_pos;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough fragment shader\r\n//\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nuniform vec4 u_camera_bbox;\r\n\r\n//\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n\t\tgl_FragColor = /*v_vColour * */texture2D( gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord );\r\n\t\tgl_FragColor.rgb *= vec3(69.0 / 256.0, 144.0 / 256.0, 142.0 / 256.0);\r\n\t\tgl_FragColor.a = v_vColour.a;\r\n}\r\n",
        "shd_shadow_tilemap",
        "#define LOWPREC lowp\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nattribute vec3 in_Position;\t\t\t// (x,y,z)\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;\t\t\t// (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord;\t\t// (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * object_space_pos;\r\n    \r\n    v_vColour = vec4(override_color.rgb, override_color.a * in_Colour.a);\r\n    v_vTexcoord =         "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n  vec4 input_color = texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord);\r\n  if (input_color.a <= 0.01) {\r\n    discard;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  gl_FragColor = v_vColour;\r\n}\r\n",

        "#define LOWPREC lowp\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW] * pos;\n\t\tfloat fogfactor = ((viewpos.z - gm_FogStart) * gm_RcpFogRange);\n\t\treturn fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nattribute vec3 in_Position;\r\nattribute float in_TexIdx;\r\nattribute vec2 in_TexCoords;\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;\r\n\r\n// general varying\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexCoords;\r\nvarying float v_vTexIdx;\r\n\r\n// this sucks: it exists because `draw_tilemap` doesn't propogate any\r\n// colors to its calls\r\nuniform vec4 override_color;\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n  gl_Position =\r\n      gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * vec4(in_Position, 1.0);\r\n\r\n  v_vTexCoords = in_TexCoords;\r\n  v_vColour = vec4(override_color.rgb, override_color.a * in_Colour.a);\r\n  v_vTexIdx = in_TexIdx;\r\n}\r\n",
        "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexCoords;\r\nvarying float v_vTexIdx;\r\n\r\n// General purpose texture slots...\r\nuniform sampler2D u_Texture0;\r\nuniform sampler2D u_Texture1;\r\nuniform sampler2D u_Texture2;\r\nuniform sampler2D u_Texture3;\r\n\r\nvec4 find_color(float f_idx, vec2 coords) {\r\n  vec4 texture_color;\r\n\r\n  // TEXTURE COLOR:\r\n  int idx = int(f_idx);\r\n  if (idx == 0) {\r\n    texture_color = texture2D(u_Texture0, coords);\r\n  } else if (idx == 1) {\r\n    texture_color = texture2D(u_Texture1, coords);\r\n  } else if (idx == 2) {\r\n    texture_color = texture2D(u_Texture2, coords);\r\n  } else {\r\n    texture_color = texture2D(u_Texture3, coords);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  return texture_color;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n  vec4 input_color = find_color(v_vTexIdx, v_vTexCoords);\r\n  if (input_color.a <= 0.01) {\r\n    discard;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  gl_FragColor = v_vColour;\r\n}\r\n",

0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 vPos;\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n    vec4 object_space_pos = vec4( in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n    gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * object_space_pos;\r\n    \r\n    v_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n    vPos = in_Position.xy;\r\n}\r\n",
        "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 vPos;\r\n\r\nuniform float performOutline;\r\nuniform float performClipRegion;\r\nuniform vec4 clipRegion;\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n  vec4 base_color = texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord);\r\n\r\n  if (performOutline > 0.5) {\r\n    vec2 offsetx = vec2(1.0 / 80.0, 0);\r\n    vec2 offsety = vec2(0, 1.0 / 80.0);\r\n\r\n    vec4 color = base_color;\r\n\r\n    color.a = max(color.a, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord + offsetx).a);\r\n    color.a = max(color.a, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord - offsetx).a);\r\n    color.a = max(color.a, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord + offsety).a);\r\n    color.a = max(color.a, texture2D(gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord - offsety).a);\r\n\r\n    if (color.a != base_color.a) {\r\n      base_color = vec4(v_vColour.rgb, 1.0);\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  if (base_color.a < 0.1) {\r\n    discard;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  if (performClipRegion > 0.5) {\r\n    base_color.a *= float(vPos.x >= clipRegion.x && vPos.y >= clipRegion.y &&\r\n                          vPos.x < clipRegion.z && vPos.y < clipRegion.w);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  base_color.a *= v_vColour.a;\r\n  // base_color.rgb *= base_color.a;\r\n\r\n  gl_FragColor = base_color;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW] * pos;\n\t\tfloat fogfactor = ((viewpos.z - gm_FogStart) * gm_RcpFogRange);\n\t\treturn fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\n//\r\n// Simple passthrough vertex shader\r\n//\r\nattribute vec3 in_Position;                  // (x,y,z)\r\n//attribute vec3 in_Normal;                  // (x,y,z)     unused in this shader.\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;                    // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord;              // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 vPos;\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n    vec4 object_space_pos = vec4( in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n    gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * object_space_pos;\r\n    \r\n    v_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n    vPos = in_Position.xy;\r\n}\r\n",

10\r\nattribute vec3 in_Position;\r\nattribute float in_TexIdx;\r\nattribute vec2 in_TexCoords;\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;\r\n\r\n// lut 7\r\nattribute float in_LutTexIdx;\r\nattribute float in_LutColumn;\r\nattribute vec3 in_LutLeftTopBot;\r\nattribute vec2 in_LutPixelSize;\r\n\r\n// clip attributes - 4\r\nattribute vec4 in_ClipRegion;\r\n\r\n// general varying\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexCoords;\r\nvarying float v_vTexIdx;\r\n\r\n// lut varying\r\nvarying float v_vLutTexIdx;\r\nvarying float v_vLutColumn;\r\nvarying vec3 v_vLutLeftTopBot;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vLutPixelSize;\r\n\r\n// clip shit\r\nvarying vec2 v_vPosition;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vClipRegion;\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n    gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * vec4(in_Position, 1.0);\r\n\r\n    v_vTexCoords = in_TexCoords;\r\n    v_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vTexIdx = in_TexIdx;\r\n\r\n    // lut\r\n    v_vLutTexIdx = in_LutTexIdx;\r\n    v_vLutColumn = in_LutColumn;\r\n    v_vLutLeftTopBot = in_LutLeftTopBot;\r\n    v_vLutPixelSize = in_LutPixelSize;\r\n\r\n    // clip\r\n    v_vPosition = in_Position.xy;\r\n    v_vClipRegion = in_ClipRegion;\r\n}\r\n",
        "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexCoords;\r\nvarying float v_vTexIdx;\r\n\r\n// lut\r\nvarying float v_vLutTexIdx;\r\nvarying float v_vLutColumn;\r\nvarying vec3 v_vLutLeftTopBot;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vLutPixelSize;\r\n\r\n// clip\r\nvarying vec2 v_vPosition;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vClipRegion;\r\n\r\n// General purpose texture slots...\r\nuniform sampler2D u_Texture0;\r\nuniform sampler2D u_Texture1;\r\nuniform sampler2D u_Texture2;\r\nuniform sampler2D u_Texture3;\r\n\r\nvec4 find_color(float f_idx, vec2 coords) {\r\n  vec4 texture_color;\r\n\r\n  // TEXTURE COLOR:\r\n  int idx = int(f_idx);\r\n  if (idx == 0) {\r\n    texture_color = texture2D(u_Texture0, coords);\r\n  } else if (idx == 1) {\r\n    texture_color = texture2D(u_Texture1, coords);\r\n  } else if (idx == 2) {\r\n    texture_color = texture2D(u_Texture2, coords);\r\n  } else {\r\n    texture_color = texture2D(u_Texture3, coords);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  return texture_color;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n  // run the clip...\r\n  if (v_vPosition.x < v_vClipRegion.x || v_vPosition.y < v_vClipRegion.y ||\r\n      v_vPosition.x > v_vClipRegion.z || v_vPosition.y > v_vClipRegion.w) {\r\n    discard;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  vec4 output_color = find_color(v_vTexIdx, v_vTexCoords);\r\n\r\n  // add in the color\r\n  output_color *= v_vColour;\r\n\r\n  // this probably breaks discard\r\n  if (output_color.a < 0.1) {\r\n    discard;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  // LUT\r\n  if (v_vLutTexIdx >= 0.0) {\r\n    float alpha = output_color.a;\r\n\r\n    // Iterate over our texture going down.....\r\n    for (float lookup_y = v_vLutLeftTopBot.y; lookup_y < v_vLutLeftTopBot.z;\r\n         lookup_y += v_vLutPixelSize.y) {\r\n      // start walking down....\r\n      vec4 lookup_color =\r\n          find_color(v_vLutTexIdx, vec2(v_vLutLeftTopBot.x, lookup_y));\r\n\r\n      bool did_find_color =\r\n          distance(lookup_color.rgb, output_color.rgb) < 0.001;\r\n\r\n      if (did_find_color) {\r\n        // and reassigning the color...\r\n        vec4 requested_color =\r\n            find_color(v_vLutTexIdx, vec2(v_vLutLeftTopBot.x +\r\n                                              v_vLutPixelSize.x * v_vLutColumn,\r\n                                          lookup_y));\r\n\r\n        // no alpha 4 u bunny\r\n        output_color = vec4(requested_color.rgb, alpha);\r\n\r\n        // and we OUTTIE\r\n        break;\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  // this is for the alpha blending\r\n  output_color.rgb *= output_color.a;\r\n\r\n  gl_FragColor = output_color;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW \t\t\t\t3\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION \t4\n#define\tMATRICES_MAX\t\t\t\t\t5\n\nuniform mat4 gm_Matrices[MATRICES_MAX]; \n\nuniform bool gm_LightingEnabled;\nuniform bool gm_VS_FogEnabled;\nuniform float gm_FogStart;\nuniform float gm_RcpFogRange;\n\n#define MAX_VS_LIGHTS\t8\n#define MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\n\n//#define\tMAX_VS_LIGHTS\t\t\t\t\t8\nuniform vec4   gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z position,  W range\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Colour[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\n\nfloat CalcFogFactor(vec4 pos)\n{\n\tif (gm_VS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tvec4 viewpos = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW] * pos;\n\t\tfloat fogfactor = ((viewpos.z - gm_FogStart) * gm_RcpFogRange);\n\t\treturn fogfactor;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn 0.0;\n\t}\n}\n\nvec4 DoDirLight(vec3 ws_normal, vec4 dir, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, dir.xyz);\n\tdotresult = min(dotresult, dir.w);\t\t\t// the w component is 1 if the directional light is active, or 0 if it isn't\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoPointLight(vec3 ws_pos, vec3 ws_normal, vec4 posrange, vec4 diffusecol)\n{\n\tvec3 diffvec = ws_pos - posrange.xyz;\n\tfloat veclen = length(diffvec);\n\tdiffvec /= veclen;\t// normalise\n\tfloat atten;\n\tif (posrange.w == 0.0)\t\t// the w component of posrange is 0 if the point light is disabled - if we don't catch it here we might end up generating INFs or NaNs\n\t{\n\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n#ifdef MIRROR_WIN32_LIGHTING_EQUATION\n\t// This is based on the Win32 D3D and OpenGL falloff model, where:\n\t// Attenuation = 1.0f / (factor0 + (d * factor1) + (d*d * factor2))\n\t// For some reason, factor0 is set to 0.0f while factor1 is set to 1.0f/lightrange (on both D3D and OpenGL)\n\t// This'll result in no visible falloff as 1.0f / (d / lightrange) will always be larger than 1.0f (if the vertex is within range)\n\t\n\t\tatten = 1.0 / (veclen / posrange.w);\n\t\tif (veclen > posrange.w)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tatten = 0.0;\n\t\t}\t\n#else\n\t\tatten = clamp( (1.0 - (veclen / posrange.w)), 0.0, 1.0);\t\t// storing 1.0f/range instead would save a rcp\n#endif\n\t}\n\tfloat dotresult = dot(ws_normal, diffvec);\n\tdotresult = max(0.0, dotresult);\n\n\treturn dotresult * atten * diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\n// general - 10\r\nattribute vec3 in_Position;\r\nattribute float in_TexIdx;\r\nattribute vec2 in_TexCoords;\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;\r\n\r\n// lut 7\r\nattribute float in_LutTexIdx;\r\nattribute float in_LutColumn;\r\nattribute vec3 in_LutLeftTopBot;\r\nattribute vec2 in_LutPixelSize;\r\n\r\n// clip attributes - 4\r\nattribute vec4 in_ClipRegion;\r\n\r\n// general varying\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexCoords;\r\nvarying float v_vTexIdx;\r\n\r\n// lut varying\r\nvarying float v_vLutTexIdx;\r\nvarying float v_vLutColumn;\r\nvarying vec3 v_vLutLeftTopBot;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vLutPixelSize;\r\n\r\n// clip shit\r\nvarying vec2 v_vPosition;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vClipRegion;\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n    gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * vec4(in_Position, 1.0);\r\n\r\n    v_vTexCoords = in_TexCoords;\r\n    v_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vTexIdx = in_TexIdx;\r\n\r\n    // lut\r\n    v_vLutTexIdx = in_LutTexIdx;\r\n    v_vLutColumn = in_LutColumn;\r\n    v_vLutLeftTopBot = in_LutLeftTopBot;\r\n    v_vLutPixelSize = in_LutPixelSize;\r\n\r\n    // clip\r\n    v_vPosition = in_Position.xy;\r\n    v_vClipRegion = in_ClipRegion;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexCoords;\r\nvarying float v_vTexIdx;\r\n\r\n// lut\r\nvarying float v_vLutTexIdx;\r\nvarying float v_vLutColumn;\r\nvarying vec3 v_vLutLeftTopBot;\r\nvarying vec2 v_vLutPixelSize;\r\n\r\n// clip\r\nvarying vec2 v_vPosition;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vClipRegion;\r\n\r\n// General purpose texture slots...\r\nuniform sampler2D u_Texture0;\r\nuniform sampler2D u_Texture1;\r\nuniform sampler2D u_Texture2;\r\nuniform sampler2D u_Texture3;\r\n\r\nvec4 find_color(float f_idx, vec2 coords) {\r\n  vec4 texture_color;\r\n\r\n  // TEXTURE COLOR:\r\n  int idx = int(f_idx);\r\n  if (idx == 0) {\r\n    texture_color = texture2D(u_Texture0, coords);\r\n  } else if (idx == 1) {\r\n    texture_color = texture2D(u_Texture1, coords);\r\n  } else if (idx == 2) {\r\n    texture_color = texture2D(u_Texture2, coords);\r\n  } else {\r\n    texture_color = texture2D(u_Texture3, coords);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  return texture_color;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid main() {\r\n  // run the clip...\r\n  if (v_vPosition.x < v_vClipRegion.x || v_vPosition.y < v_vClipRegion.y ||\r\n      v_vPosition.x > v_vClipRegion.z || v_vPosition.y > v_vClipRegion.w) {\r\n    discard;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  vec4 output_color = find_color(v_vTexIdx, v_vTexCoords);\r\n\r\n  // add in the color\r\n  output_color *= v_vColour;\r\n\r\n  // this probably breaks discard\r\n  if (output_color.a < 0.1) {\r\n    discard;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  // LUT\r\n  if (v_vLutTexIdx >= 0.0) {\r\n    float alpha = output_color.a;\r\n\r\n    // Iterate over our texture going down.....\r\n    for (float lookup_y = v_vLutLeftTopBot.y; lookup_y < v_vLutLeftTopBot.z;\r\n         lookup_y += v_vLutPixelSize.y) {\r\n      // start walking down....\r\n      vec4 lookup_color =\r\n          find_color(v_vLutTexIdx, vec2(v_vLutLeftTopBot.x, lookup_y));\r\n\r\n      bool did_find_color =\r\n          distance(lookup_color.rgb, output_color.rgb) < 0.001;\r\n\r\n      if (did_find_color) {\r\n        // and reassigning the color...\r\n        vec4 requested_color =\r\n            find_color(v_vLutTexIdx, vec2(v_vLutLeftTopBot.x +\r\n                                              v_vLutPixelSize.x * v_vLutColumn,\r\n                                          lookup_y));\r\n\r\n        // no alpha 4 u bunny\r\n        output_color = vec4(requested_color.rgb, alpha);\r\n\r\n        // and we OUTTIE\r\n        break;\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  // this is for the alpha blending\r\n  output_color.rgb *= output_color.a;\r\n\r\n  gl_FragColor = output_color;\r\n}\r\n",
        "in_LutTexIdx",
        "in_LutColumn",
        "in_LutLeftTopBot",
        "in_LutPixelSize",
        "in_ClipRegion",
        "__yy_sdf_shader",
        "#define LOWPREC lowp\n#define\tMATRIX_VIEW \t\t\t\t\t0\n#define\tMATRIX_PROJECTION \t\t\t\t1\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD \t\t\t\t\t2\n#define\tMATRIX_WORLD_VIEW  gm_AmbientColour;\t\t\t\t\t\t\t// rgb=colour, a=1\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_Direction[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t// normalised direction\nuniform vec4   gm_Lights_PosRange[MAX_VS_LIGHTS];\t\t\t// X,Y,Z objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\n//\r\n// SDF vertex shader\r\n//\r\nattribute vec3 in_Position;                  // (x,y,z)\r\n//attribute vec3 in_Normal;                  // (x,y,z) v_vColour;\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n    vec4 object_space_pos = vec4( in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n    gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * object_space_pos;\r\n    \r\n    v_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n}\r\n",
        "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\n//\r\n// SDF fragment shader\r\n//\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n\tvec4 texcol = texture2D( gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord );\r\n\t\r\n\tfloat spread = fwidth(texcol.a);\t\r\n\tspread = max(spread * 0.75, 0.001);\t\r\n\ttexcol.a = smoothstep(0.5 - spread, 0.5 + spread, texcol.a);\t\t\t\r\n\t\r\n\tvec4 combinedcol = v_vColour * texcol;\r\n\tDoAlphaTest(combinedcol);\t\r\n\t\t\t\r\n    gl_FragColor = combinedcol;\r\n}\r\n",

diffusecol;\n}\n\nvec4 DoLighting(vec4 vertexcolour, vec4 objectspacepos, vec3 objectspacenormal)\n{\n\tif (gm_LightingEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\t// Normally we'd have the light positions\\\\directions back-transformed from world to object space\n\t\t// But to keep things simple for the moment we'll just transform the normal to world space\n\t\tvec4 objectspacenormal4 = vec4(objectspacenormal, 0.0);\n\t\tvec3 ws_normal;\n\t\tws_normal = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacenormal4).xyz;\n\t\tws_normal = normalize(ws_normal);\n\n\t\tvec3 ws_pos;\n\t\tws_pos = (gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD] * objectspacepos).xyz;\n\n\t\t// Accumulate lighting from different light types\n\t\tvec4 accumcol = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);\t\t\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoDirLight(ws_normal, gm_Lights_Direction[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor(int i = 0; i < MAX_VS_LIGHTS; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\taccumcol += DoPointLight(ws_pos, ws_normal, gm_Lights_PosRange[i], gm_Lights_Colour[i]);\n\t\t}\n\n\t\taccumcol *= vertexcolour;\n\t\taccumcol += gm_AmbientColour;\n\t\taccumcol = min(vec4(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0), accumcol);\n\t\taccumcol.a = vertexcolour.a;\n\t\treturn accumcol;\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\treturn vertexcolour;\n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\n//\r\n// SDF vertex shader\r\n//\r\nattribute vec3 in_Position;                  // (x,y,z)\r\n//attribute vec3 in_Normal;                  // (x,y,z)     unused in this shader.\r\nattribute vec4 in_Colour;                    // (r,g,b,a)\r\nattribute vec2 in_TextureCoord;              // (u,v)\r\n\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n    vec4 object_space_pos = vec4( in_Position.x, in_Position.y, in_Position.z, 1.0);\r\n    gl_Position = gm_Matrices[MATRIX_WORLD_VIEW_PROJECTION] * object_space_pos;\r\n    \r\n    v_vColour = in_Colour;\r\n    v_vTexcoord = in_TextureCoord;\r\n}\r\n",
        "#version 120\n#define LOWPREC \n#define lowp\n#define mediump\n#define highp\n#define precision\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_AlphaTestEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tif (SrcColour.a <= gm_AlphaRefValue)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdiscard;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nvoid DoFog(inout vec4 SrcColour, float fogval)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSL_ 1\n//\r\n// SDF fragment shader\r\n//\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n\tvec4 texcol = texture2D( gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord );\r\n\t\r\n\tfloat spread = fwidth(texcol.a);\t\r\n\tspread = max(spread * 0.75, 0.001);\t\r\n\ttexcol.a = smoothstep(0.5 - spread, 0.5 + spread, texcol.a);\t\t\t\r\n\t\r\n\tvec4 combinedcol = v_vColour * texcol;\r\n\tDoAlphaTest(combinedcol);\t\r\n\t\t\t\r\n    gl_FragColor = combinedcol;\r\n}\r\n",
        "__yy_sdf_effect_shader",
        "precision mediump float;\n#define LOWPREC lowp\n// Uniforms look like they're shared between vertex and fragment shaders in GLSL, so we have to be careful to avoid name clashes\n\nuniform sampler2D gm_BaseTexture;\n\nuniform bool gm_PS_FogEnabled;\nuniform vec4 gm_FogColour;\nuniform bool gm_AlphaTestEnabled;\nuniform float gm_AlphaRefValue;\n\nvoid DoAlphaTest(vec4 SrcColour)\n{\n\tif (gm_PS_FogEnabled)\n\t{\n\t\tSrcColour = mix(SrcColour, gm_FogColour, clamp(fogval, 0.0, 1.0)); \n\t}\n}\n\n#define _YY_GLSLES_ 1\n//\r\n// SDF (with effects) fragment shader\r\n//\r\nvarying vec2 v_vTexcoord;\r\nvarying vec4 v_vColour;\r\n\r\n// SDF values are measured from 0 (at the outer edge) to 1 which is the innermost point that can be represented\r\nuniform bool gm_SDF_DrawGlow;\t\t\t\t// whether the glow effect is enabled\r\nuniform vec2 gm_SDF_Glow_MinMax;\t\t\t// the SDF range across which the glow fades\r\nuniform vec4 gm_SDF_Glow_Col;\t\t\t\t// the colour of the glow\r\n\r\nuniform bool gm_SDF_DrawOutline;\t\t\t// whether the outline effect is enabled\r\nuniform float gm_SDF_Outline_Thresh;\t\t// the SDF distance which represents the outer edge of the outline\r\nuniform vec4 gm_SDF_Outline_Col;\t\t\t// the colour of the outline\r\n\r\nuniform float gm_SDF_Core_Thresh;\t\t\t// the SDF distance which represents the outer edge the shape\r\nuniform vec4 gm_SDF_Core_Col;\t\t\t\t// the colour of the core part of the shape\r\n\r\nvoid main()\r\n{\r\n\tvec4 texcol = texture2D( gm_BaseTexture, v_vTexcoord );\r\n\t\t\r\n\tfloat gm_SDF_Glow_MinMax.y, texcol.a);\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\t\r\n\t\r\n\t// Handle outline effect\r\n\tif (gm_SDF_DrawOutline)\r\n\t{\r\n\t\tif (texcol.a > (gm_SDF_Outline_Thresh - pixelspread))\r\n\t\t{\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\tblendfactor = smoothstep(gm_SDF_Outline_Thresh - pixelspread, gm_SDF_Outline_Thresh + pixelspread, texcol.a);\r\n\t\t\tif (currcol.a < 0.0)\r\n\t\t\t{\r\n\t\t\t\tcurrcol = vec4(gm_SDF_Outline_Col.r,gm_SDF_Outline_Col.g,gm_SDF_Outline_Col.b, 0.0);\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\tcurrcol = mix(currcol, gm_SDF_Outline_Col,
